//Cairo Cairo Tower Zamalek, Cairo Governorate The Cairo Tower is a free-standing concrete tower, Its 187m. Tahrir Square El-Tahrir Square, Qasr an Nile Tahrir Square, also known as "Martyr Square", is a major public town square. Abdeen Palace El-Gomhoreya Square, Rahbet Abdin, Abdeen A historic Cairo palace, and one of the official residences . Cairo Opera House Opera Land، EL GEZIRAH، Zamalek Part of Cairo National Cultural Center, is the main performing arts venue. //Alex Citadel of Qaitbay As Sayalah Sharq, Qesm Al Gomrok, Alexandria Governorate A defensive fortress located on the Mediterranean sea coast. Montaza Palace Al Mandarah Bahri, Qism El-Montaza, Alexandria Governorate A palace, museum and extensive gardens. Alexandria Zoo Ezbet Saad, Qism Sidi Gabir, Alexandria Governorate Which allows guests to walk around the zoo and view a selection of animals from around the world.
//Giza Great Sphinx Al Haram, Giza Governorate A limestone statue of a reclining sphinx, a mythical creature with the body of a lion and the head of a human Giza pyramid complex Al Haram, Giza Governorate An archaeological site on the Giza Plateau, on the outskirts of Cairo.
//Luxor Karnak El-Karnak, Luxor, Luxor Governorate Comprises a vast mix of decayed temples, chapels, pylons, and other buildings. Valley of the Queens El-Karnak, Luxor, Luxor Governorate A place in Egypt where wives of Pharaohs were buried in ancient times. Mummification Museum Luxor City, Luxor, Luxor Governorate An archaeological museum.It is dedicated to the art of Ancient Egyptian mummification.
